The article is a press briefing by a senior administration official on Vice President Biden's upcoming trip to Southeastern Europe. The trip will consist of visits to Bosnia-Herzegovina, Serbia, and Kosovo. In Bosnia-Herzegovina, the Vice President will meet with the Bosnian tri-presidency and address the Parliament. In Serbia, he will meet with President Tadic and the Defense Minister, and attend a dinner hosted by President Tadic. In Kosovo, the Vice President will meet with the President, Prime Minister, and Assembly Speaker, and address the Assembly. The objective of the trip is to demonstrate intensified U.S. engagement in the region and support for the Euro-Atlantic community. The Vice President's personal history with the region and his past efforts to end violence and ethnic cleansing in Bosnia and Kosovo are also highlighted. The trip is seen as a refocus on the Balkans and a commitment to strong United States' support for the region.